The article is a press briefing by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs and OMB Director Peter Orszag. They discuss the "pay as you go" proposal by the administration and its importance in restoring fiscal discipline. They also discuss the deficit neutrality of healthcare reform and the need to address rising Medicare and Medicaid costs. They address concerns about exceptions to PAYGO rules and the use of TARP funds. They also discuss the timeline for Judge Sotomayor's confirmation hearings and the administration's position on Guantanamo Bay detainees.